  "notes": [
    "D-030 scale x1.00 HELPED but did NOT fully slim the legs: the master's legs are proportionally SHORT (radial span only ~66mm even at Labrador size), while the RS00 knuckle is a fixed \u00d854. So each femur/tibia neck is only ~26mm \u2014 the knuckles are now separated by a short neck (vs fully MERGED at 272mm) but the leg still reads knobbly/chunky, not slender. The master legs are ~66mm vs the D-030 DESIGN leg of 280mm \u2014 the movie Rocky simply has stubby squat legs. Three-way tension: movie-squat legs vs long-slender look vs fixed \u00d846 RS00. To truly slim: fewer knuckles/leg, or lengthen the legs past the master (less movie-accurate), or accept the knobbly rock aesthetic (fits an Eridian).",
    "PRINT SPLIT: the recursive dovetail/dowel splitter is wired in, but at this segmentation NO single printed part exceeds 250mm (largest = thorax core ~190mm). The ~400mm carapace is the ASSEMBLED span (leg-tip to leg-tip), not one part: it is already divided into the central thorax core (r<62), 5 coxa dome-shoulders, and the 5 seated carapace plates. So no split fires; the machinery (\u00d86 dowel keys, longest-axis bisection) is ready if parts grow.",
    "Hands are the REAL grip_hand.stl (palm+3 fingers+crown), seated at each tip in the standing pose (separate multi-piece grip print assembly, not fused)."
  ],
